*[[1872]] &amp;ndash; [[Samuel Morse|Samuel F. B. Morse]], American painter and inventor of the [[telegraph]] (b. 1791)
*[[1891]] &amp;ndash; [[Albert Pike]], American Confederate Brigadier General, envoy, author, attorney, and Freemason (b. 1809)
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; [[Esther Hobart Morris|Esther Morris]], American [[Justice of the Peace]]  (b. 1814)
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Johann Ludwig von Heyse|Paul von Heyse]], German writer, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel laureate]] (b. 1830)
*[[1922]] &amp;ndash; [[Hermann Rorschach]], Swiss psychologist (b. 1884)
*[[1928]] &amp;ndash; [[Theodore William Richards]], American chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel laureate]] (b. 1868)
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; [[Zauditu of Ethiopia]] (b. 1876)
*[[1933]] &amp;ndash; [[K. S. Ranjitsinhji]], Indian king and Test cricketer (b. 1872)
*[[1936]] &amp;ndash; [[Jean Baptiste Eugène Estienne]], French general (b. 1860)
*[[1953]] &amp;ndash; [[Hugo Sperrle]], German field marshal (b. 1885)
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; [[Tudor Davies]], Welsh tenor (b. 1892)
*  1958   &amp;ndash; [[Josei Toda]], Japanese educator and peace activist,  second president of [[Soka Gakkai]] (b. 1900)
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[C. S. Forester]], English author (b. 1899)
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; [[Franz Halder]], German general (b. 1884)
*  1972   &amp;ndash; [[Toshitsugu Takamatsu]], Japanese Martial Arts Grandmaster (b. 1887)
*  1972   &amp;ndash; [[Gil Hodges]], American baseball player and manager (b. 1924)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Georges Pompidou]], French politician, President of France (b. 1911)
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Walter Wolf (politician)|Walter Wolf]], German politician (b. 1907)
*[[1987]] &amp;ndash; [[Buddy Rich]], American jazz drummer and bandleader (b. 1917)
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Tomisaburo Wakayama]], Japanese actor  (b. 1929)
*  1992   &amp;ndash; [[Juan Gómez González]], Spanish football player  (b. 1954)
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Betty Furness]], American actress (b. 1916)
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; [[Harvey Penick]], American golf instructor (b. 1904)
*  1995   &amp;ndash; [[Hannes Alfvén]], Swedish physicist (b. 1908)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Rob Pilatus]], American model, dancer, and singer ([[Empire Bizarre]], [[Milli Vanilli]], [[The Real Milli Vanilli]], and [[Rob &amp; Fab]]) (b. 1965)
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[Tommaso Buscetta]], Sicilian mafioso (b. 1928)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Daudelin]], Canadian artist (b. 1920)
*  2001   &amp;ndash; [[Jennifer Syme]], American actress (b. 1972)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Levi Celerio]], Filipino composer and lyricist (b. 1910)
*  2002   &amp;ndash; [[John R. Pierce]], American engineer and author (b. 1910)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Edwin Starr]], American singer (b. 1942)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[John Argyris]], Greek aeronautical engineer (b. 1913)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Betty Bolton]], British actress (b. 1906)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Pope John Paul II]] (b. 1920)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Bernard Seigal]], American musician, music critic and writer ([[Beat Farmers]]) (b. 1957)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Lloyd Searwar]], Guyanese diplomat (b. 1925)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Nina Schenk Gräfin von Stauffenberg]], German widow of [[Claus Schenk Graf von Stauffenberg]] (b. 1913)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Reed (actor)|Paul Reed]], American actor (b. 1909)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Henry L. Giclas]], American astronomer (b. 1910)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul Arden]], British Author and advertiser (b. 1940)
*  2008   &amp;ndash; [[Ray Poole]], American football player (b. 1921)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Albert Sanschagrin]], Canadian Roman Catholic bishop (b. 1911)
*  2009   &amp;ndash; [[Bud Shank]], American saxophonist and flautist ([[The L.A. Four (group)|The L.A. Four]]) (b. 1926)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Mike Cuellar]], Cuban baseball player (b. 1937)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Chris Kanyon]], American wrestler (b. 1970)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Thomas J. Moyer]], American jurist, Chief Justice of the [[Supreme Court of Ohio]] (b. 1939)
*[[2011]] &amp;ndash; [[John C. Haas]], American businessman and philanthropist (b. 1918)
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; [[Jesús Aguilarte]], Venezuelan army captain and politician, Governor of [[Apure]] State in [[Venezuela]] (b. 1959)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Warren Bonython]], Australian conservationist, explorer, author, and chemical engineer, creator of the [[Heysen Trail]] (b. 1916)
